Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly decreased total protein, which may indicate nutritional or hepatic issues. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Renal function should be further evaluated and monitored.
